><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_6648969\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_6648969\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dqd1713426128184.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dqd1713426128184.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dqd1713426128184.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jel1665702784236\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies a unique string to be used as a key in calculating the hash-values used to protect non-editable fields from being modified in a web browser.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"jel1665702784236__topic_d144035e1_d144036e1_d144037e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jel1665702784236__p_d144038e1_d144039e1_d144040e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$SERVER_SECRET</span> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> } <var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jel1665702784236__section_bwn_chn_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274316e64\">Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jel1665702784236__p_d144044e1_d144045e1_d144046e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>—unique string, with a\n            maximum length of 369 characters. The string should be long, complex, and hard to guess;\n            for example, at least 64 characters and a combination of upper and lowercase characters,\n            numbers, and symbols.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jel1665702784236__section_gsq_dhn_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274316e75\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jel1665702784236__table_d17438e1_d17439e1_d17440e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"ph filepath\">wasv.asn</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[WEB]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Generated during installation</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jel1665702784236__section_an5_ghn_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274316e122\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jel1665702784236__p_d144053e1_d144054e1_d144055e1\">To protect parts of the data that the DSP sends to\n            the browser, such as NED fields and occurrence IDs, the server uses the\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$server_secret</code> setting. The server protects NED fields with a\n            hash-value that it generates using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$server_secret</code> setting. On an\n            AJAX request, this hash-value is sent back with the field data to the server, the server\n            recalculates the hash-value, and compares it with the original. If the hash-values are\n            the same, the field data is unchanged and accepted by the server. If the hash-values are\n            not the same, a security error is generated, and any further server-side processing\n            should stop.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jel1665702784236__p_d144056e1_d144057e1_d144058e1\">During installation, Uniface generates a unique key\n            and assigns it to this setting, but you can provide your own key.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"jel1665702784236__note_ovv_3hn_lwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The key should be kept secret,\n      so you need to control access to the assignment file of the Web Application Server (by\n      default, <span class=\"ph filepath\">wasv.asn</span>) so that only the Uniface Server\n        (<code class=\"ph codeph\">userver</code>) process can read it.</div>\n<p class=\"p\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"jel1665702784236__pre_l5v_3hn_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[WEB]\n$SERVER_SECRET = JIOhcvjsqj8vsadv;394hwe028*&amp;^ijhe8762l;v93kns2-0gvr;b-05nm2k3;lkcv;flb0-76-u76-0g45nj348h&amp;^Z</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/key1665702908800.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Application Configuration and Deployment</a><p>When you deploy and configure the web application you need to ensure that the application is securely deployed. To do so, the passwords and security mechanisms provided with Uniface must be changed and secured.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6648969\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6648969\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$SERVER_SECRET Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies a unique string to be used as a key in calculating the hash-values used to protect non-editable fields from being modified in a web browser. $SERVER_SECRET { = } Value Values Value —unique string, with a maximum length of 369 characters. The string should be long, complex, and hard to guess; for example, at least 64 characters and a combination of upper and lowercase characters, numbers, and symbols. Defaults Assignment file: wasv.asn Section: [WEB] Default value: Generated during installation Description To protect parts of the data that the DSP sends to the browser, such as NED fields and occurrence IDs, the server uses the $server_secret setting. The server protects NED fields with a hash-value that it generates using the $server_secret setting. On an AJAX request, this hash-value is sent back with the field data to the server, the server recalculates the hash-value, and compares it with the original. If the hash-values are the same, the field data is unchanged and accepted by the server. If the hash-values are not the same, a security error is generated, and any further server-side processing should stop. During installation, Uniface generates a unique key and assigns it to this setting, but you can provide your own key. CAUTION: The key should be kept secret, so you need to control access to the assignment file of the Web Application Server (by default, wasv.asn ) so that only the Uniface Server ( userver ) process can read it. For example: [WEB] $SERVER_SECRET = JIOhcvjsqj8vsadv;394hwe028*&^ijhe8762l;v93kns2-0gvr;b-05nm2k3;lkcv;flb0-76-u76-0g45nj348h&^Z Copy Related Links Web Application Configuration and Deployment When you deploy and configure the web application you need to ensure that the application is securely deployed. To do so, the passwords and security mechanisms provided with Uniface must be changed and secured. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}